Package: xtop
Version: 0.39.0-1
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Architecture: amd64
Depends: libc6
Recommends: journalctl, docker-compose, postgresql-client
Installed-Size: 23240
Maintainer: Farhan Tahir <farhan.003@gmail.com>
Homepage: https://github.com/ftahirops/xtop
Description: Incident-first root-cause analysis console for Linux
 xtop is a terminal-based system monitor with ranked root-cause hypotheses,
 evidence scoring, and eBPF deep diagnostics. v0.39.0 adds a multi-host
 fleet hub with embedded web dashboard, incident diff vs prior similar
 events, auto-correlated config drift and app logs, a runbook library,
 post-mortem tooling, VM right-sizing (xtop cost) and named utilization
 baselines.
